    "Moreover, personality perceptions are linked with likability: Many of the least likable figures (e.g., Lee Harvey Oswald, Charles Manson, and both Kims) appear repeatedly on the socially undesirable (i.e., low) extrema of the perceived personality trait.",
    "As detailed in Table 2, public figures' likability, birth year, and gender significantly correlate with perceived personality in our sample.",
